{
  "stem": "3382.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They disbanded all Jewish life, practically-- Zionists in Zion-- and disbanded the school-- Tarbut school.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they sent me to teach in Yiddish school and in the other school.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I got tremendous load.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I had a full load-- 42 hours in one school, an additional eight hours-- and that's 50, 50 hours.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I had to go to make time, you know, to be on time, I had to-- almost to run from one school to another school because they were in different parts of, of the city.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] All right, so when Soviets-- and here, I want to tell you now example of incidents or accidents.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The Lithuanians were in Vilna.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So they had embassies of foreign powers-- and Japanese embassy and Swedish embassy, it seems to me; and it seems some Portuguese, too, you know-- used to give away visas-- transit visas-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] transit visas, you know, to-- and many of refugees in Vilna.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There was probably about 15,000 refugees in Vilna now from Poland.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And first, all the Zionists' hierarchy from all sorts, you know-- the Chalutz, and Center, and Betarim-- Betar, Jabotinsky people, you know-- so everybody tried to get the visa and get out.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in December, 1939, I went to Lida.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So yeah-- so I told Sula, look, definitely I, as an academic man with doctorate degree and published work, and so on, I can get a visa either through Sweden or to Sweden or Japan east.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then probably I would be able somehow to go south maybe-- I don't know, whether America-- I wouldn't know if America wouldn't let in, but I-- probably to Australia.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So she said to me, look, my parents are here in Lida.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Without them, I won't go.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
